The paper proposes a neural network model for time series forecasting with exogenous variables. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG and cs.AI. The model uses LSTM, which is a type of recurrent neural network, and the paper discusses the attention mechanism used to interpret variable importance. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance using real datasets and a synthetic dataset, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
